parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the Continuously Variable Transmission (CVT) can cause the vehicle to lose power, hesitate, or fail to engage in gear, leading to accidents or stranding the driver.
symptoms: The vehicle hesitates or fails to accelerate
the transmission slips or hesitates
the vehicle shudders or vibrates
the transmission makes a knocking sound
the vehicle goes into "limp mode".

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the door lock system can cause the doors to open unintentionally while driving, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The doors open while driving
the locks release unexpectedly
the door opens with excessive pressure applied.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Loss of Power and Unpredictable Acceleration
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The loss of power and unpredictable acceleration can cause accidents, especially in heavy traffic or when merging onto highways.
symptoms: The vehicle loses power
hesitates
or accelerates erratically
the vehicle "kangaroos" or surges forward
no engine codes or warning lights appear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the FEB system can cause the vehicle to suddenly brake or lose power while driving, which can lead to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The FEB warning light appears on the dashboard
the vehicle suddenly brakes or loses power
the vehicle stalls or cuts out
the battery warning light appears
the vehicle is unable to shift gears.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of sensors, particularly the front sensors, can cause the FEB system to malfunction, leading to sudden braking or loss of power, which can result in accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The FEB warning light appears on the dashboard
the vehicle suddenly brakes or loses power
the vehicle stalls or cuts out
the battery warning light appears.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Electronic defects can cause a range of issues, including the malfunction of the FEB system, loss of power, and inability to shift gears, which can lead to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle loses power
the vehicle is unable to shift gears
the FEB warning light appears on the dashboard
the battery warning light appears.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden and unexplained shattering of the sunroof can cause a loud noise, distraction, and potential injury to occupants from flying glass, which can lead to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: Loud popping noise
sunroof shattering without any apparent cause or warning
sudden and unexpected failure of the sunroof.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden and unexplained shutdown of the engine while driving can cause loss of power, loss of control, and increase the risk of accidents, especially in hazardous weather conditions.
symptoms: Engine shuts off without warning
engine and collision sensor lights illuminate
vehicle must be stopped and restarted to continue driving
no warning lamps or symptoms prior to shutdown.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The backup camera blindspot can cause the driver to be unaware of obstacles or vehicles behind the vehicle, increasing the risk of accidents and injuries.
symptoms: The backup camera does not display the entire area behind the vehicle
there is a blindspot on the backup camera
the vehicle's alarm system does not indicate the presence of an obstacle or vehicle.
